bib_record.title: Interaction of B-11 with Bi-209 and Ta-181 targets at intermediate energies.

free_txt: Energy resolution of 0.23% at an energy 1332 keV
Uncertainty in the cross section depended on
the statistical significance of experimental results,
the accuracy in measuring the target thickness and the
accuracy of tabular data on nuclear constants, and the
uncertainty in determining the detector efficiency with
allowance for the accuracy in calculating its energy
Errors in measurements of target thickness
and accuracy of tabular data on nuclear constants
The intensity of B-11 beam was 17 nA. The irradiation
Bi-209 and Ta-181 targets were used. The target was a
stack consisted of 0.65 mu-m and 9.5 mu-m thick foils,
and catcher 47 mu-m thick Al foils.
